{
  "text": "Additional supporting information may be found in the online version of this article: Table S1Genes encoding members of pathways involved in the ENS development As a service to our authors and readers, this journal provides supporting information supplied by the authors. Such materials are peer-reviewed and may be re-organised for online delivery, but are not copy-edited or typeset. Technical support issues arising from supporting information (other than missing files) should be addressed to the authors. HSCR. ∫: Mouse Genome Informatics search tool; phenotype refers only to gut/ENS system. *: % of isolated HSCR patients with coding region mutations in these genes, data from (Heanue & Pachnis, 2007 , Amiel & Lyonnet, 2001 [CITATION_1] . -: no patients with isolated HSCR reported. #: Referred from Human disease model [CITATION_2] or mouse model [CITATION_3] ",
